1. HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol)
	- HTTP is a protocol that help the application communicate with backend APIs
	- What is resources: For example, if you manage students of the school, then every student is an resource
2. Method
  - HEAD: return status code (200, 300, 400)
  - GET: return one or list of resource
  - POST: submit resource to the server
  - PATCH: change only some data of resource
  - PUT: will override the whole data of resource except the ID
  - DELETE: remove the data
